.\" cyw43455.4 — manual page for the cyw43455 CYW43455 SDIO WiFi driver
.\"
.Dd June 12, 2026
.Dt CYW43455 4
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm cyw43455
.Nd Cypress CYW43455 802.11ac SDIO WiFi driver
.Sh SYNOPSIS
To load the driver as a module at boot time place the following lines in
.Xr loader.conf 5 :
.Bd -literal -offset indent
cyw43455_load="YES"
.Ed
.Pp
To also preload the firmware images (required when the module loads before the
root filesystem is mounted — see
.Sx FIRMWARE DELIVERY
below):
.Bd -literal -offset indent
brcm_fw_bin_load="YES"
brcm_fw_bin_name="/boot/firmware/cyw43455/brcmfmac43455-sdio.bin"
brcm_fw_bin_type="firmware"
brcm_fw_nvram_load="YES"
brcm_fw_nvram_name="/boot/firmware/cyw43455/brcmfmac43455-sdio.txt"
brcm_fw_nvram_type="firmware"
brcm_fw_clm_load="YES"
brcm_fw_clm_name="/boot/firmware/cyw43455/brcmfmac43455-sdio.clm_blob"
brcm_fw_clm_type="firmware"
.Ed
.Sh DESCRIPTION
The
.Nm
driver provides support for the Cypress (Broadcom) CYW43455 802.11ac + BT 5.0
combo chip as found on the Raspberry Pi 5.
The driver covers the WLAN SDIO path (functions F0–F2); Bluetooth is a
separate milestone.
.Pp
The chip is a FullMAC design: the 802.11 MAC and PHY run inside the chip's
ARM CR4 firmware.
The driver downloads the firmware binary and NVRAM configuration at attach
time, then communicates via SDPCM-framed BCDC IOVARs over SDIO function F2.
.Sh FIRMWARE DELIVERY
Firmware files are
.Em not
embedded in
.Pa cyw43455.ko .
They are loaded at attach time through the
.Xr firmware 9
subsystem from
.Pa /boot/firmware/cyw43455/ :
.Bl -tag -width "brcmfmac43455-sdio.clm_blob"
.It Pa brcmfmac43455-sdio.bin
ARM CR4 firmware binary.
Required; attach fails without it.
.It Pa brcmfmac43455-sdio.txt
NVRAM key=value configuration file.
Required; attach fails without it.
.It Pa brcmfmac43455-sdio.clm_blob
Regulatory domain (CLM) blob.
Optional; if absent the chip operates in a limited-channels mode with
a warning in
.Xr dmesg 8 .
.El
.Pp
The
.Xr firmware 9
subsystem provides two delivery paths:
.Bl -enum
.It
.Em kldload path :
After the root filesystem is mounted,
.Xr firmware 9
reads the files lazily from disk on a dedicated taskqueue thread that has
filesystem context.
No special
.Xr loader.conf 5
configuration is needed for this path.
.It
.Em Loader preload path :
When
.Nm
is loaded by the boot loader (via
.Va cyw43455_load="YES"
in
.Xr loader.conf 5 )
before the root filesystem is mounted, there is no filesystem context.
The SYNOPSIS block above shows the required
.Xr loader.conf 5
entries that instruct the loader to preload each binary image into kernel
memory as a
.Dq firmware
object; the driver then obtains them from RAM without any disk access.
.El
.Pp
The CLM blob is intentionally delivered as a file rather than a compiled-in
firmware module (as
.Xr iwmfw 4
and similar drivers do) so that the regulatory domain can be swapped
per-deployment without rebuilding the driver.
Replace
.Pa brcmfmac43455-sdio.clm_blob
with a jurisdiction-appropriate blob and reload the module.
.Sh SYSCTLS
The following
.Xr sysctl 8
variables are available under
.Va hw.cyw43455 :
.Bl -tag -width "firmware_version"
.It Va debug
Bitmask enabling verbose
.Xr dmesg 8
output:
.Bl -tag -width "0x4"
.It 0x1
Firmware image loading and download progress.
.It 0x2
SDIO hardware probing (EROM scan, KSO, TCM RAM size, SR detection).
.It 0x4
Post-release bring-up (CSR states, HT clock, F2 enable, handshake).
.El
Can be set at boot via
.Xr loader.conf 5 :
.Va hw.cyw43455.debug="7"
.It Va chip_id
Chip ID read from ChipCommon (0x4345 for CYW43455).
.It Va chip_rev
Chip revision (6 for the Pi 5 variant).
.It Va firmware_version
Firmware version string reported by the
.Dq ver
IOVAR after boot.
.It Va fw_wsec , Va fw_wpa_auth , Va fw_auth
Live firmware security state (wsec cipher mask, wpa_auth key-mgmt mask,
auth type).
Read-only; each read issues a live firmware IOVAR GET.
Only valid once the SDPCM layer is running.
.El
.Sh FILES
.Bl -tag -width "/boot/firmware/cyw43455/brcmfmac43455-sdio.clm_blob"
.It Pa /boot/modules/cyw43455.ko
Kernel module.
.It Pa /boot/firmware/cyw43455/brcmfmac43455-sdio.bin
Firmware binary.
.It Pa /boot/firmware/cyw43455/brcmfmac43455-sdio.txt
NVRAM configuration.
.It Pa /boot/firmware/cyw43455/brcmfmac43455-sdio.clm_blob
Regulatory domain blob (optional).
.El
.Sh DIAGNOSTICS
.Bl -diag
.It "cyw0: firmware image %q unavailable; ..."
Firmware file missing or inaccessible.
For boot-time use add the preload block to
.Xr loader.conf 5 .
For
.Xr kldload 8
use, ensure the file exists under
.Pa /boot/firmware/cyw43455/ .
Other causes include securelevel policy and
.Va debug.firmware_max_size
being too small.
.It "cyw0: CLM blob %q not found, limited channels may be available"
The
.Pa brcmfmac43455-sdio.clm_blob
file is absent.
The driver continues without it but regulatory channel constraints may not be
enforced.
Not fatal.
.It "cyw0: fw handshake timeout: ..."
The firmware did not assert HMB_DATA_FWREADY within 1 second of HOSTINTMASK
being written.
Subsequent IOVAR transactions will fail.
.It "cyw0: cyw_attach: pm IOVAR failed"
The
.Dq pm
(power management) IOVAR is rejected by this firmware version.
Non-fatal; the driver continues without power management control.
.El
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr firmware 9 ,
.Xr sdiob 4 ,
.Xr loader.conf 5 ,
.Xr kldload 8 ,
.Xr dmesg 8
.Sh HISTORY
The
.Nm
driver was written for FreeBSD/arm64 on the Raspberry Pi 5.
.Sh BUGS
Bluetooth is not yet supported.
The driver uses polling rather than interrupt-driven SDIO I/O.
WPA/WPA2 association is implemented but 802.11r fast BSS transition and
802.11w management frame protection are not.
